# Git Workflow

Remote: `git@github-legacy:Overton77/humanupgradebiotechapi` (branch: main)
Deploy target: Vercel (project: humanupgradeapi, scope: overtons-projects)

## Small changes (bug fixes, config tweaks, single-file edits)

1. Edit directly on `main`
2. `git add . && git commit -m "descriptive message"`
3. `git push origin main`

## Large changes (new features, schema changes, multi-file refactors)

1. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feat/<name>`
2. Implement the feature with atomic commits
3. Push the branch: `git push -u origin feat/<name>`
4. Deploy preview: `vercel deploy -y --no-wait --scope overtons-projects`
5. Verify health: `vercel curl /api/health --deployment <url> --scope overtons-projects`
6. Verify GraphQL: `vercel curl /api/graphql --deployment <url> --scope overtons-projects -- -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"query":"{ podcasts { id } }"}'`
7. Merge to main and push: `git checkout main && git merge feat/<name> && git push origin main`
8. Production deploy: `vercel deploy --prod -y --no-wait --scope overtons-projects`

## What counts as "large"

- Any Prisma schema change (new model, new field, enum change)
- New GraphQL queries/mutations or input type changes
- New resolver files or DataLoader additions
- Adding dependencies
- Changes touching 5+ files
